{"type":null,"faqId":34744,"title":" How do I set my phone to work as a modem and provide Internet access for computers?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.s1{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\n.s2{font-weight:bold;}\n.s3{font-family:微软雅黑;}\n.p1{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p2{margin-bottom:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Book Antiqua;font-size:9pt;}\n.p3{margin-left:1.4409722in;margin-top:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;}\n.p4{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>On the home screen, touch </span><span class=\"s2\">Settings</span><span>.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>In </span><span class=\"s2\">WIRESS &amp; NETWORKS</span><span>, touch </span><span class=\"s2\">More…</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s2\">Tethering &amp; portable hotspot</span><span>. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>Select </span><span class=\"s2\">USB tethering</span><span>. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">1.  </span><span>Install the driver using HiSuite. On the computer, right-click </span><span class=\"s2\">My computer</span><span> and choose </span><span class=\"s2\">Management</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s2\">Device Manager</span><span> from the shortcut menu. The new network adapter is displayed. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110594\" style=\"width:0.59375in;height:0.16666667in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p  >\n<span>When using USB tethering, your phone's mobile data connection must be turned on. Otherwise, the phone cannot provide Internet access for the computer. </span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p4\"></p>\n<p class=\"p4\">\n<span>If a computer provides a wireless network adapter, you can turn on </span><span class=\"s2\">Portable Wi-Fi hotspot</span><span class=\"s3\">.</span><span> Then the computer can connect to your phone over Wi-Fi to access the Internet. Currently, this function is available to computers running Windows. </span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"9484","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1436871808000,"seriesProductName":"H30-L02","visitedTimes":1,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"HONOR 3C LTE (H30-L02)","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}